# Netlify redirect rules. Vite copies web/public/* into dist/, so this ships with the SPA.
#
# Rule 1 — API proxy. Status 200 makes this a *rewrite* (a server-side proxy), not a
# browser redirect: the URL bar stays on netlify.app, so the httpOnly session cookie the
# Render server sets is stored first-party. This is what lets us keep the same-origin
# cookie design while the API lives on a different host.
#
# !! Replace the host below with your real Render service URL (Render dashboard → your
#    service → the .onrender.com URL at the top). :splat forwards the rest of the path.
/api/*  https://drawbridge-web.onrender.com/api/:splat  200

# Rule 2 — SPA fallback. Everything else serves the app shell so client-side routes and
# hard refreshes / deep links don't 404. Must come AFTER the /api rule.
/*      /index.html  200
